{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "615454d70b0506ac499b46a9", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": null, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": null, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "NTAS1", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76e4c52ffa3c944600e1"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eba2"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [{"title": "NTA Abhyas Paper", "value": "03", "isVisible": true}], "previousYearPapers": [], "question": {"text": "A light ray moving in medium-I (of refractive index <math><msub><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></math>) is incident on interface of two media and it is totally internally reflected at the interface. Now, refractive index <math><msub><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></math> of medium-II is decreased, then<br />\r<br />\r<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/nta_abhyas/neet/images/335310q.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 146px;\" />", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "Divss", "text": "ray will move completely parallel to the interface", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "HaH6q", "text": "ray will be still totally internally reflected at interface", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}, {"id": "yiU12", "text": "ray will be totally transmitted into medium-II only, if angle of incidence is increased", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "Twe6b", "text": "ray will be totally transmitted in medium-II", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "As <math><msub><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></math> decreases, <math><msub><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">sin</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mrow></math> also decreases.<br /><br />So, condition <math><mi>i</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow></msub></math> is still satisfied and there will be still total internal reflection at interface. If angle of incidence is increased, then ray will be still totally internally reflected at interface because <math><mi>i</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow></msub></math>.", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f48314dab", "61a8a2c2e8ce0dc8a5c62d2d", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352b", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7d", "616056cd0283de43c87e3e15", "616057190283de43c87e3e18", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd7", "64d50bd73df7f4a7f3017f6f", "66b79b34d4b564dfab4f94cc", "678ea9a09cc79e5f592bdc11", "67fa5fef4468eb1307ceb0ad", "6807d2ad647479b8e8696479"], "cpyqbChapters": ["61964c922db938c3ec5c87e8", "6160243a86b518ff2afd9379", "6160243ae896b71d7f0f03d9", "61bb820fc1f688a120dfda9f", "61964c9102fe1de035852896", "61e7bd71a2dd607688d6c01b", "61c08989e3eba41a9e71354b", "61602437a04b762ba7dfcb47", "61602438690b07c861db4cc9", "6160243b7384a30f11cacc9e", "629109ef0299d67104ca49d5", "629f3a9295d059d5cc4d982e", "629621243e04d5d8ca7b92bd", "629f390e4eb9140dc965900d", "64eb06dd3118f713ecfef1b0", "66d5853ba75f05ee8564f575", "67921d651d5b5072da5e9aae", "67fdff46378e1624ea7b6984", "680920293a10446a207fdecb"], "cpyqbExams": ["616059d70283de43c87e3e24", "616059730283de43c87e3e22"]}}